climbs.name: Mouthful of Gank
climbs.fa: Cameron Burns and Paul Fehlau, March 1990

content.description: This unremarkable route is as bad as the name sounds and only worth climbing if you're desperate for a tick - otherwise keep on walking to nearby Dutzi Rock which offers much better climbing than this pile.
content.location:
Just right of

Fistful of Bush

.

climbs.name: Freddy vs Jason
climbs.fa: Alan Bartlett and Dan Zacks, Jan 2004

content.description: Two pitch route at the two-tiered NE corner of the main massive Anthrax Rock.  P1 goes up a right-facing overhanging corner, made easy by the amply featured left face, to top out onto the left side of the midway terrace.  P2 ascends the upper fun (albeit short) dihedral crack to the back and on the right side of the midway terrace, going from tight hands to hands to jugs over the roof bulge.

climbs.name: Fistful of Bush
climbs.fa: Cameron Burns and Paul Fehlau, March 1990

content.description: At the right end of the east aspect of Anthrax Rock is a smooth, short buttress. A 2 bolt face climb (Mouthful Of Gank) goes up this buttress. Immediately left is a wide crack with a bush 5' up from the start. If you haven't gotten any lately, be sure to get a left-handed, back-handed, undercling of the bush, as you move through the crux.
content.protection: small cam for just right of the bush

climbs.name: Bride Of Chucky
climbs.fa: Alan Bartlett and Dan Zacks, Jan 2004

content.description: Up the grainy and chossy starting blocks that might detract a bit.  Then up nice crack, past a featured mid-face, to a high thin crack that ends at a horizontal, then pull up and over onto slick-feeling slab that starts a runout that quickly becomes more featured and easier toward the summit.
content.location: Down scramble to climber's right, down a rocky gully that would drop down just to the right of the start.
